Supplementary Fig. 2 | Left. Background Kemp elimination rates in 20 mM TRIS, pH 8.0 (black) and $2 0 ~ \mathsf { m M }$ TRIS, $\mathsf { p H 8 . 0 }$ with 1 mM ascorbate, 100 nM superoxide dismutase (SOD), and 20 nM catalase (red). Presented traces are the average of three runs. Right. Initial rates of the Kemp elimination catalyzed by FerrElCat at $\mathsf { p H } 8 . 0$ under different conditions: averaged rates using three different batches of protein of FerrElCat (each in triplicate, a total of 9 measurements) done in $2 0 ~ \mathsf { m M }$ TRIS, $\mathsf { p H 8 } . 0$ with 1 mM ascorbate, 100 nM SOD, and 20 nM catalase (left); rates averaged over three runs on one protein batch using in $2 0 ~ \mathsf { m M }$ TRIS, $\mathsf { p H 8 . 0 }$ with 1 mM ascorbate, 100 nM SOD, and 20 nM catalase (middle) and rates averaged over three runs using in 20 mM TRIS, $\mathsf { p H 8 . 0 }$ on the same protein batch as the measurements in the middle sample (right). Substrate concentration $7 0 0 ~ \mu \mathrm { M }$ . Data are presented as the mean values and the error bars represent standard deviations obtained from three independent measurements.

